dc_description_s:
Note: This service is only for using online; full resolution downloads are not supported.Image service presenting natural color, leaf-off imagery primarily from the 2015 WI Regional Orthophoto Consortium (WROC), the Southeast WI Regional Planning Commission (SEWRPC), and other individual county air photo projects. Flights occurred in the Spring of 2015 for 49 Wisconsin counties. Resolution of the 2015 aerial photography ranges from 3 inches to 12 inches. 

Flights occurred in the Spring of 2016 for 2 counties.

For 9 WI counties where neither 2016 nor 2015 aerial photography is available, natural color, leaf-off air photos from 2013 & 2014 are included (pixel resolution ranging from 4 inches to 1 meter). For the remaining 12 WI counties, natural color, leaf-off aerial photography from the 2010 WROC is included (pixel resolution of 18 inches).  For information about WROC 2015, see: http://www.ncwrpc.org/WROC2015/. Please see the companion WI DNR layer, Wisconsin Leaf-Off Digital Orthophotography - Index, for the year of air photo acquisition, pixel resolution, and source image format for each county presented in this image service.WI DNR recognizes the following organizations for making source data available: All counties participating in the Wisconsin Regional Orthophoto Consortium (WROC) 2015 & 2010, Southeast WI Regional Planning Commission (SEWRPC), Brown County, Calumet County, Door County, Douglas County, City & County of Eau Claire, Green Lake County, Outagamie County, Pepin County, Pierce County, Rusk County, and Washburn County.For more information, contact https://dnr.wi.gov/feedback and select the Subject Geographic Information System Data.
